race.description: Apco Service Stations Banjo Paterson Handicap
race.comment: CATALONA (14) was an emphatic Maiden winner over 1600m at Ballarat with today's rider Declan Bates engaged. Deserved that and has plenty of scope for improvement. Maps well and can go on with the job. POWERBOUND (1) was allowed to drift back from an outside draw but found the line strongly beaten a long neck over 1620m at Donald. Will have to do it the hard way again, but the extra metres suit. FONN POWER (10) continues to improve and can get into the finish at each-way odds. UP AND UNDER (4) improved narrowly beaten at Geelong and then found the grade too tough at Pakenham. He's been freshened at is a hope back to this level. HALF CROWN (11) will be fitter and won't be far away with average luck in the run.
